Root cause: macos-latest is arm64, so bazel build produced arm64 binaries for BOTH matrix entries. The x86_64 DMG had an arm64 sidecar that could not execute on Intel Macs. Fix: macos-latest-large gives an Intel runner for native x86_64 builds. Also unified all platforms to use Bazel (Windows was still Cargo), removed the separate frontend CI job (Bazel genrule handles it), and added CLAUDE.md directive about comprehensive changes after user feedback about half-implementations.
